nodes.name: AltBn128

nodes.documentation:
@dev g1YFromX computes a Y value for a G1 point based on an X value.
This computation is simply evaluating the curve equation for Y on a
given X, and allows a point on the curve to be represented by just
an X value + a sign bit.
nodes.name: g1YFromX

nodes.documentation:
@dev g2YFromX computes a Y value for a G2 point based on an X value.
This computation is simply evaluating the curve equation for Y on a
given X, and allows a point on the curve to be represented by just
an X value + a sign bit.
nodes.name: g2YFromX

nodes.documentation:
@dev Hash a byte array message, m, and map it deterministically to a
point on G1. Note that this approach was chosen for its simplicity /
lower gas cost on the EVM, rather than good distribution of points on
G1.
nodes.name: g1HashToPoint

nodes.documentation:
@dev Calculates whether the provided number is even or odd.
@return 0x01 if y is an even number and 0x00 if it's odd.
nodes.name: parity

nodes.documentation: @dev Compress a point on G1 to a single uint256 for serialization.
nodes.name: g1Compress

nodes.documentation: @dev Compress a point on G2 to a pair of uint256 for serialization.
nodes.name: g2Compress

nodes.documentation: @dev Decompress a point on G1 from a single uint256.
nodes.name: g1Decompress

nodes.documentation: @dev Unmarshals a point on G1 from bytes in an uncompressed form.
nodes.name: g1Unmarshal

nodes.documentation: @dev Marshals a point on G1 to bytes form.
nodes.name: g1Marshal

nodes.documentation: @dev Unmarshals a point on G2 from bytes in an uncompressed form.
nodes.name: g2Unmarshal

nodes.documentation:
@dev Wrap the scalar point multiplication pre-compile introduced in
Byzantium. The result of a point from G1 multiplied by a scalar should
match the point added to itself the same number of times. Revert if the
provided point isn't on the curve.
nodes.name: scalarMultiply

nodes.documentation:
@dev Wrap the pairing check pre-compile introduced in Byzantium. Return
the result of a pairing check of 2 pairs (G1 p1, G2 p2) (G1 p3, G2 p4)
nodes.name: pairing

devdoc.details: Implementations of common elliptic curve operations on Ethereum's (poorly named) alt_bn128 curve. Whenever possible, use post-Byzantium pre-compiled contracts to offset gas costs. Note that these pre-compiles might not be available on all (eg private) chains.
devdoc.title: Operations on alt_bn128
